# Create Page Guide – Stellar Frontend

Use this guide to create a new page using the existing system. Follow the patterns below.

---

## 1. Project Structure

```
src/
├── pages/              # Page components (one file per page, or folder for complex pages)
│   ├── Accounts.tsx
│   ├── Channels.tsx
│   ├── google/         # Feature-scoped pages
│   └── tiktok/
├── services/           # API layer (api.ts base + domain services)
├── hooks/              # React Query hooks
│   ├── queries/        # useQuery hooks
│   └── mutations/      # useMutation hooks
├── components/         # Reusable components
│   ├── ui/             # Base UI (Button, Card, Input, etc.)
│   └── layout/         # Sidebar, DashboardHeader, Layout
├── contexts/          # AuthContext, DateRangeContext, SidebarContext, etc.
├── routes/             # Route definitions
├── utils/              # pageTitle, urlHelpers, formatters, etc.
└── lib/                # queryClient
```

---

## 2. Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|-------------|----------|
| **Page file** | PascalCase, descriptive | `Accounts.tsx`, `GoogleCampaigns.tsx` |
| **Page component** | Same as file, exported | `export const Accounts: React.FC = () => {...}` |
| **Service** | camelCase + `Service` or `service` | `accountsService`, `googleAdwordsCampaignsService` |
| **Query hook** | `use` + Entity + Purpose | `useAccountsPaginated`, `useChannels` |
| **Mutation hook** | `use` + Action + Entity | `useCreateAccount`, `useUpdateAccount` |
| **Route path** | kebab-case, nested by domain | `/brands`, `/brands/:accountId/integrations` |

