## 3. API Pattern

**Base:** `src/services/api.ts` – axios instance with `API_BASE_URL`, auth interceptors, token refresh.

**Service module pattern:**
```ts
// src/services/myEntity.ts
import api from "./api";

export interface MyEntity {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  // ...
}

export const myEntityService = {
  getList: async (params?: Record<string, string>): Promise<MyEntity[]> => {
    const { data } = await api.get<MyEntity[]>("/my-entity/", { params });
    return data;
  },
  getById: async (id: number): Promise<MyEntity> => {
    const { data } = await api.get<MyEntity>(`/my-entity/${id}/`);
    return data;
  },
  create: async (payload: Partial<MyEntity>): Promise<MyEntity> => {
    const { data } = await api.post<MyEntity>("/my-entity/", payload);
    return data;
  },
  update: async (id: number, payload: Partial<MyEntity>): Promise<MyEntity> => {
    const { data } = await api.patch<MyEntity>(`/my-entity/${id}/`, payload);
    return data;
  },
  delete: async (id: number): Promise<void> => {
    await api.delete(`/my-entity/${id}/`);
  },
};
```

**Backend URL mapping:**
- Accounts: `/api/accounts/`
- Channels: `/api/accounts/<accountId>/channels/`
- Google Ads: `/api/google-adwords/<accountId>/channels/<channelId>/...`
- Auth: `/api/auth/`, `/api/users/`

---

## 3b. How to Integrate with the API

### Auth

The `api` instance automatically adds the auth token to every request:
- Token is stored in `localStorage.getItem("accessToken")`
- Sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`
- On 401: backend `/auth/refresh/` is called; if refresh fails, user is redirected to `/login`
- Never pass the token manually – the interceptor handles it

### GET vs POST for List Endpoints

| Endpoint type | Method | Use when |
|---------------|--------|----------|
| Simple list (no filters) | `GET` | Accounts, channels – use `params` for pagination |
| Filtered list | `POST` | Campaigns, keywords, targets – send `{ filters }` in body |
| Detail | `GET` | Single entity by ID |
| Create/Update/Delete | `POST` / `PUT` / `PATCH` / `DELETE` | As expected |

```ts
// Simple list – GET with params
const { data } = await api.get("/accounts/", { params: { page: 1, page_size: 10 } });

// Filtered list – POST with body (backend expects filters in body)
const { data } = await api.post(url, { filters: { campaign_name__icontains: "test", state__in: ["Enable"] } });
```

### Response Formats

| Type | Shape | Example |
|------|-------|---------|
| Paginated (DRF) | `{ count, next, previous, results }` | Accounts list |
| Custom list | `{ campaigns: [...] }` or `{ keywords: [...] }` | Campaigns, keywords |
| Create/update | Entity object or `{ id, name, ... }` | Single object |
| Error | `{ error: string }` or `{ detail: string }` | 4xx/5xx |

Handle both shapes when backend varies:
```ts
const data = response.data;
const list = Array.isArray(data) ? data : (data?.results ?? data?.campaigns ?? []);
```

### Error Handling

```ts
try {
  const result = await myEntityService.create(payload);
  setSuccessMessage("Created!");
} catch (err: any) {
  const msg = err.response?.data?.error ?? err.response?.data?.detail ?? "Request failed";
  setError(msg);
}
```

- `err.response.status` – 400, 401, 403, 404, 500
- `err.response.data` – backend error payload
- 401 triggers auto token refresh, then redirect to login on failure

### Environment

- `VITE_API_BASE_URL` – defaults to `http://localhost:8000/api`
- Set in `.env`: `VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.example.com/api`

