## 6. Route Registration

Add route in `src/routes/`:

**Account-scoped (no channel):**
```tsx
<Route path="/brands/:accountId/my-page" element={
  <ProtectedRoute>
    <WorkspaceRequiredRoute>
      <AccountRequiredRoute>
        <BrandAccessRoute>
          <Layout><MyNewPage /></Layout>
        </BrandAccessRoute>
      </AccountRequiredRoute>
    </WorkspaceRequiredRoute>
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />
```

**Channel-scoped (Google/TikTok – needs channelId):**
```tsx
<Route path="/brands/:accountId/:channelId/google/campaigns" element={
  <ProtectedRoute>
    <WorkspaceRequiredRoute>
      <AccountRequiredRoute>
        <BrandAccessRoute>
          <GoogleSyncStatusWrapper>
            <Layout><GoogleCampaigns /></Layout>
          </GoogleSyncStatusWrapper>
        </BrandAccessRoute>
      </AccountRequiredRoute>
    </WorkspaceRequiredRoute>
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />
```

**Route wrappers:**
- `ProtectedRoute` – requires auth
- `WorkspaceRequiredRoute` – requires workspace selection
- `AccountRequiredRoute` – requires account in URL
- `BrandAccessRoute` – requires brand access
- `GoogleSyncStatusWrapper` – for Google Ads pages (sync status context)
- `Layout` – provides PasswordUpdateBanner, VerifyEmailBanner, main wrapper

